Route Remarks:

A582
BISIG-TELEN
(1) RNP10 approval required from FL290 and above.FPL Item 10a: R, Item 18: PBN/A1.
(2) Class A radar surveillance airspace. VHF radio as primary DCPC.
(3) Class A remote airspace. CPDLC as primary DCPC. HF radio as alternative communication channel via third-party ATS unit.
(4) Flight crew option for datalink ADS-C/CPDLC.FPL Item 10a: J, P2, Item 10b: D1, Item 18: SUR/RSP180 COM/RCP240.
(5) Fifty (50) NM procedural longitudinal separation minima for RNP10 aircraft pair in:
a. radar surveillance airspace or,
b. remote airspace using ADS-C/CPDLC.
(6) Southwest bound uni-directional route from FL280 and above. For FL Series refer to ENR 1.8-6 Table 2.2.4.
